<TITLE> BNP to set out budget proposals Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)  Main opposition BNP will set out its views and proposals on the budget for the next fiscal year on Monday afternoon. Chairperson Khaleda Zia will place the proposals at the Sheraton Hotel at 4pm, her press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan told bdnews24.com. Finance minister AMA Muhith is set to table the national budget for 2010-11 financial year on June 10. Political leaders, economists, businessmen, intellectuals, editors of national dailies, professionals, civil society representatives and envoys of foreign missions have been invited to the programme. Meanwhile BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain hinted that his party will not join parliament on the day budget is to be placed and will monitor it on television from the party chief's Gulshan office. 
